## 4.2 Module Description

The system is built from **6 independent, composable modules** under [modules/](file:///c:/Users/Aman/OneDrive/Desktop/Projects/ALM4.0%28Ollama%29/app.py#307-324). Each module has a single, well-defined responsibility.

---

### 📥 Module 1 — `preprocessing/` · `AudioPreprocessor`

**Purpose:** Standardise raw audio input into a consistent format for all downstream modules.

**Key Operations:**
- Loads audio files (WAV, MP3, M4A, FLAC, OGG) using `librosa` / `pydub`
- Resamples to **16 000 Hz mono** for model compatibility
- Normalises amplitude to prevent clipping
- Returns a NumPy array and sample rate

**Inputs:** Raw audio file (path)  
**Outputs:** [(audio: np.ndarray, sr: int)](file:///c:/Users/Aman/OneDrive/Desktop/Projects/ALM4.0%28Ollama%29/app.py#391-1051), duration, peak amplitude

---

### 🗣️ Module 2 — [speech/](file:///c:/Users/Aman/OneDrive/Desktop/Projects/ALM4.0%28Ollama%29/modules/context/adapter.py#238-245) · `SpeechRecognizer`

**Purpose:** Convert speech audio into text using OpenAI Whisper.

**Key Operations:**
- Runs the [base](file:///c:/Users/Aman/OneDrive/Desktop/Projects/ALM4.0%28Ollama%29/modules/reasoning/inference_engine.py#104-181) Whisper model locally (no internet required after download)
- Auto-detects language with support for Hindi, English, and more
- Returns transcript text, detected language, and confidence
- Temperature set to `0.0` for deterministic output

**Inputs:** [(audio: np.ndarray, sr: int)](file:///c:/Users/Aman/OneDrive/Desktop/Projects/ALM4.0%28Ollama%29/app.py#391-1051)  
**Outputs:** [SpeechData](file:///c:/Users/Aman/OneDrive/Desktop/Projects/ALM4.0%28Ollama%29/modules/context/adapter.py#38-44) — `{ transcript, language, confidence }`

---

### 🔊 Module 3 — `sound_detection/` · `SoundDetector`

**Purpose:** Identify environmental and background sound events using Google's YAMNet CNN.

**Key Operations:**
- Loads YAMNet from TensorFlow Hub
- Returns top-5 sound labels above the confidence threshold (default 0.3)
- Groups events into categories: speech, traffic, machinery, environmental, ambient, structural

**Inputs:** [(audio: np.ndarray, sr: int)](file:///c:/Users/Aman/OneDrive/Desktop/Projects/ALM4.0%28Ollama%29/app.py#391-1051)  
**Outputs:** [SoundDetectionData](file:///c:/Users/Aman/OneDrive/Desktop/Projects/ALM4.0%28Ollama%29/modules/context/adapter.py#45-50) — `{ events: [{label, confidence}], primary_event }`

---

### 😊 Module 4 — [emotion/](file:///c:/Users/Aman/OneDrive/Desktop/Projects/ALM4.0%28Ollama%29/modules/context/adapter.py#253-260) · `EmotionAnalyzer`

**Purpose:** Classify the emotional state of the speaker from vocal audio features.

**Key Operations:**
- Extracts **MFCC (Mel-Frequency Cepstral Coefficients)** from audio
- Maps feature vectors to 8 emotion classes: `neutral`, `calm`, `happy`, `sad`, `angry`, `fearful`, `disgust`, `surprised`
- Returns the dominant emotion with a confidence score

**Inputs:** [(audio: np.ndarray, sr: int)](file:///c:/Users/Aman/OneDrive/Desktop/Projects/ALM4.0%28Ollama%29/app.py#391-1051)  
**Outputs:** [EmotionAnalysisData](file:///c:/Users/Aman/OneDrive/Desktop/Projects/ALM4.0%28Ollama%29/modules/context/adapter.py#31-37) — `{ emotional_state, confidence, vocal_tension }`

---

### 🔗 Module 5 — [context/](file:///c:/Users/Aman/OneDrive/Desktop/Projects/ALM4.0%28Ollama%29/modules/reasoning/inference_engine.py#871-908) · Three Sub-components

#### 5a. `ContextIntegrator`
Merges transcript, detected sounds, and emotion into a unified text context block for downstream consumption.

#### 5b. [SemanticAnalyzer](file:///c:/Users/Aman/OneDrive/Desktop/Projects/ALM4.0%28Ollama%29/modules/context/semantic_analyzer.py#132-444) *(Layer 2)*
Analyses the transcript text against curated keyword banks:

| Bank | Examples |
|---|---|
| Emergency | `help`, `hurt`, `ambulance`, `trapped`, `fire` |
| Injury | `bleeding`, `broken`, `unconscious`, `pain` |
| Medical | `asthma`, `seizure`, `overdose`, `cardiac` |
| Conflict | `gun`, `fight`, `weapon`, `threat` |
| Vulnerability | `baby`, `child`, `elderly`, `please help` |
| Guidance/Dispatch | `stay on the phone`, `call 911`, `are you safe` |

Computes a **risk score (0–1)** and classifies the situation into: `emergency`, `medical`, `conflict`, `public_event`, or `normal_conversation`.

#### 5c. [DataAdapter](file:///c:/Users/Aman/OneDrive/Desktop/Projects/ALM4.0%28Ollama%29/modules/context/adapter.py#61-369)
Orchestrates merging of all module outputs into a single unified dictionary and formats it as a structured Ollama prompt.

**Inputs:** Outputs of all modules 1–4 + semantic analysis  
**Outputs:** Merged context `Dict`, formatted prompt [str](file:///c:/Users/Aman/OneDrive/Desktop/Projects/ALM4.0%28Ollama%29/modules/reasoning/inference_engine.py#648-665)

---

### 🧠 Module 6 — [reasoning/](file:///c:/Users/Aman/OneDrive/Desktop/Projects/ALM4.0%28Ollama%29/modules/reasoning/inference_engine.py#410-441) · [InferenceEngine](file:///c:/Users/Aman/OneDrive/Desktop/Projects/ALM4.0%28Ollama%29/modules/reasoning/inference_engine.py#73-1441)

**Purpose:** Produce the final structured scene report using a local LLM or deterministic fallback.

**Key Operations:**
- Connects to a locally running **Ollama** server (`http://localhost:11434`)
- Sends a structured prompt with the system message (emergency reasoning AI persona)
- Parses the LLM response into clean fields (`location`, `people`, `activity`, [emotion](file:///c:/Users/Aman/OneDrive/Desktop/Projects/ALM4.0%28Ollama%29/modules/context/adapter.py#253-260), [risk_level](file:///c:/Users/Aman/OneDrive/Desktop/Projects/ALM4.0%28Ollama%29/modules/context/semantic_analyzer.py#349-370), `confidence`, `summary`)
- Handles `>` separator and newline-separated LLM output formats
- Falls back to rule-based deterministic logic if Ollama is unreachable or returns an empty response

**LLM Parameters:**
```
temperature : 0.2   (low for consistent, factual output)
num_predict : 400   (token limit for focused responses)
```

**Inputs:** Merged context `Dict`, risk analysis `Dict`  
**Outputs:** Formatted report [str](file:///c:/Users/Aman/OneDrive/Desktop/Projects/ALM4.0%28Ollama%29/modules/reasoning/inference_engine.py#648-665) displayed in the UI and available for download

